<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Samurai on Balance Guides</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/samurai/</link><description>Recent content in Samurai on Balance Guides</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 06 Aug 2025 01:39:28 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/samurai/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Best in Slot (BiS)</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/samurai/best-in-slot/</link><pubDate>Wed, 06 Aug 2025 01:39:28 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/samurai/best-in-slot/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Openers</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/samurai/openers/</link><pubDate>Wed, 06 Aug 2025 01:31:53 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/samurai/openers/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="standard-opener"&gt;Standard Opener&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Used in the majority of encounters. Due to phasing, in some instances it may be best to begin with Kasha into Gekko instead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
